### Additional Conditions for Allowable Expenses  

Note to Supplier:  
To the extent the Commonwealth approves the inclusion of any travel and accommodation expenses as Allowable Expenses: :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}  

- the maximum amount payable would be the amount that would be payable to a non-SES Commonwealth Officer for fares and overnight accommodation in respect of the travel under policies of Defence.  
- the Supplier would be required to complete a Travel Plan in the CMS Travel Module CMS Access for DPN Users. For non-DPN users and travel types not supported by the CMS Travel Module, the Supplier must use the Domestic Travel Approval Form (AF090) to plan the travel. More information about the CMS Travel Module is available from the TravelConnect Tools page.  
- All Allowable Expenses must be pre-approved in writing by the Commonwealth.  
- All other travel-related expenses, such as meals and incidentals, are the responsibility of the Supplier. :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}  

